content:
{
  "plan": "Round 1 begins. Initiative order: Bandit (14), Bandit 2 (13), Scout Kira (8), Eirik Hearthwise (4). All creatures alive and prepared for combat. No actions taken yet this round. Await Bandit to begin.",
  "narration": "The morning mist clings low among the broken stones of the weathered North Tower Overlook, shrouding the ancient watchtower in ghostly haze. The silent bell frame swings gently above, ominously still. Suddenly, sharp movement catches your eye from the concealed brush—two rugged bandits emerge, eyes wary and weapons drawn to halt any meddling. Beside you, Scout Kira readies her shortbow, fingers tightening on the shaft of an arrow. The daggers and scimitars of your foes glint menacingly in the soft dawn light.\n\nThe tension snaps as the first bandit steps forward, scanning for a threat. The battle for the tower's fate has begun. The bandits act swiftly, then Kira, then your turn lies ahead. Steel and faith shall be your allies. Brace yourself, Eirik Hearthwise—the enemy strikes first.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, Bandit acts first. Initiative order: Bandit (14), Bandit 2 (13), Scout Kira (8), Eirik Hearthwise (4). Bandit will use their two attacks: first scimitar, then light crossbow. Both attacks resolved using preroll d20 values 15 and 5. Await outcome of attacks and damage rolls from generic dice pool for Bandit. Player turn is not active yet. Combat round remains 1 until all creatures have acted.",
  "narration": "The lead bandit snarls, eyes narrowing as he lunges forward with his curved scimitar. The blade arcs sharp and fast, aiming to end the fight quickly. When the sting of steel misses its mark, the bandit doesn't hesitate, whisking up a light crossbow and loosing a bolt with deadly intent.\n\nThe dawn light glints off the edge of his blade, cold and merciless. Your heart hammers—this is no skirmish, but a battle for control over the tower. The second bandit tenses, ready to follow his companion's lead.\n\nStand steady, Eirik Hearthwise. Your chance to act will come once the bandits finish their assault.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 continuing. Bandit's first attack roll 15 against Eirik's AC 16 is a MISS with scimitar. Second attack roll 5 with light crossbow also misses. No damage applied to Eirik (HP remains 11). Bandit_2's turn next with two attacks: scimitar attack roll 10 and light crossbow attack roll 7 against Eirik's AC 16. Await attack outcomes and damage resolution for Bandit_2. Scout Kira and Eirik act afterward. Combat round remains 1 until all alive creatures have acted.",
  "narration": "The bandit lunges forward, scimitar arcing through the air—but your scale mail fleetly deflects the blow, the blade clanging loudly against the sturdy armor. Undeterred, the bandit quickly sets up his light crossbow and fires, but the bolt whizzes past you into the mist, missing by a wide margin.\n\nNo wounds mar your flesh, but the urgency of the fight sharpens; the second bandit steps forward, eyes blazing with intent. The battle for the North Tower Overlook continues.\n\nBrace yourself, Eirik Hearthwise—your turn draws near, but first the second bandit advances.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 continuing. Bandit_2's first attack roll is 10 against Eirik's AC 16, which misses. Second attack roll is 7, also a miss. Scout Kira will act next with two attacks: shortbow (attack roll 13) and shortsword (attack roll 4) against the leading bandit AC 12. Await outcomes and damage resolution for Scout Kira's attacks. Combat round 1 remains active until all alive combatants have acted.",
  "narration": "The second bandit advances with predatory eyes, swinging his scimitar in a sweeping arc. But your armor's resilience holds firm, and the blade finds only empty air. He frowns, switching swiftly to his light crossbow, firing a bolt that whistles past without finding a target.\n\nFrom beside you, Scout Kira rises like a shadow, nocking an arrow with practiced ease. Her shortbow twangs, sending a deadly shaft toward the foremost bandit. As the arrow flies, she prepares to draw her shortsword for a swift follow-up strike.\n\nThe bandits' aim falters—for now, the pressure shifts toward your allies. Stand ready, Eirik; your moment is close at hand.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 continuing. Scout Kira's shortbow attack roll 13 hits Bandit (AC 12). Damage roll is 6 from d6 plus 3 modifier, total 9 damage. Bandit HP reduces from 11 to 2. Kira's shortsword attack roll 4 misses Bandit AC 12. Next up is Eirik Hearthwise's turn. Combat round 1 remains active until all living creatures complete their turns.",
  "narration": "Scout Kira's arrow strikes true, piercing the bandit's armor and tearing a deep wound. The bandit staggers, clutching the bleeding injury as blood seeps through his garb, reducing his strength visibly. She follows with a swift attempt of her shortsword, but the bandit parries the attack, buying himself a moment's respite.\n\nThe battle hangs in balance with the bandit badly weakened but still on his feet. Now, Eirik Hearthwise, the next move is yours. How will you press the attack?",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit takes 9 piercing damage from Kira's shortbow, HP from 11 to 2."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 continuing. Eirik Hearthwise declared a light crossbow attack on Bandit with AC 12. Awaiting player to roll d20 plus +3 to hit. If hit, then roll 1d8 plus 1 for damage. Scout Kira's actions complete. Bandit_2 yet to act. Combat round 1 remains active until all creatures have acted.",
  "narration": "You steady your light crossbow, the morning mist swirling around the ancient stone tower as you take careful aim at the wounded bandit clutching his side. The bolt whistles as it streaks through the air, seeking to finish the fight your ally began.\n\nRoll a d20 and add +3 to see if your bolt finds its mark against the bandit's armor. The fate of this skirmish may hinge on this shot.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 continuing. Eirik Hearthwise's attack roll is 17 + 3 = 20, which hits Bandit with AC 12. Awaiting player's damage roll: 1d8 + 1. Combat round 1 remains active until all alive creatures have completed their turns.",
  "narration": "Your bolt streaks through the misty morning air, striking true against the weakened bandit. The impact sends him staggering backward, a grimace crossing his face as the bolt pierces armor and flesh alike. You stand ready to unleash the full force of your attack—roll 1d8 and add 1 to see how much damage your bolt deals.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 is complete with all living creatures having acted in initiative order: Bandit (dead), Bandit_2 (acted), Scout Kira (acted), and Eirik Hearthwise (acted). Bandit died from Eirik's attack reducing HP to 0. Combat round increments to 2, with Bandit_2 acting first this round as the lone remaining enemy alive in initiative order.",
  "narration": "With a final, shuddering gasp, the first bandit collapses, his threat extinguished beneath your bolt. The stench of sweat and blood mingles with the morning mist as the second bandit snarls in fury, stepping forward to renew the assault. Scout Kira narrows her eyes and tightens her grip on her bow, poised for the next exchange.\n\nThe tower's fate hangs in the balance as the second round of combat begins. Bandit_2 moves first—steel and shadows converge once again. Steady yourself, Eirik Hearthwise. What do you do next?",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit dies after taking 2 piercing damage from Eirik's light crossbow; HP 0, status dead."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 begins with Bandit_2 acting first, followed by Scout Kira and then Eirik Hearthwise (player). Bandit_2 will make two attacks: scimitar and light crossbow using prerolls 5 and 19. Scout Kira will follow with two attacks: shortbow and shortsword using prerolls 8 and 7. The player waits for their turn to act after NPCs and monsters have completed their actions.",
  "narration": "The first bandit lies motionless, a silent testament to the brutal strike you just delivered. Now, the second bandit steps forward, eyes blazing with renewed fury, gripping his scimitar tightly. Nearby, Scout Kira quietly readies her bow, her sharp gaze never leaving the enemy.\n\nBefore you can make your move, the second bandit lunges in, weapon flashing. Scout Kira follows with precise shots of her own. Their attacks are swift—but the moment you have been waiting for is almost here.\n\nHold steady, Eirik Hearthwise. The tide of battle turns with your next move. Stand ready—your turn comes next. What do you do?",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 continuing. Bandit_2's first attack roll is 5 against Eirik's AC 16, which misses. Second attack roll is 19, which hits Eirik. Await damage roll from generic dice for Bandit_2's light crossbow attack. Scout Kira's turn will follow next. Combat round 2 remains active until all alive creatures complete their turns.",
  "narration": "The second bandit rushes forward, swinging his scimitar with clumsy force but missing as you step back just in time. Frustrated but undeterred, he brings up his light crossbow—his bolt whistles through the mist and finds its mark, thudding painfully into your arm.\n\nYou grit your teeth against the sting as the fight intensifies. Scout Kira narrows her eyes and prepares to counterattack, her bowstring already taut. The clash continues—hold your ground, Eirik Hearthwise. Your moment to strike approaches swiftly.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 continuing. Bandit_2's light crossbow attack hits Eirik. Using generic d6 damage roll 1 + 1 (Dex modifier) for total 2 damage. Eirik's HP reduced from 11 to 9. Scout Kira will act next. Player turn follows Scout Kira's actions. Combat round 2 remains active until all alive creatures have acted.",
  "narration": "The bandit's bolt bites sharply into your arm, the sharp sting momentarily stealing your breath. You bleed but remain unbowed, the pain fueling your resolve. The morning air tastes sharp with tension as Scout Kira draws her bowstring, ready to retaliate.\n\nYour battle-worn armor shields you from worse harm, but the threat remains real. Gather your strength, Eirik Hearthwise—your turn is just moments away.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Eirik Hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 2 piercing damage from Bandit_2's light crossbow attack. HP reduced from 11 to 9."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 continuing. Scout Kira attacks bandit_2 with shortbow (attack roll 8, misses) and shortsword (attack roll 7, hits). Shortsword damage roll uses d6 3 plus 3 modifier = 6 damage. Bandit_2 HP reduces from 11 to 5. After Scout Kira's turn, Eirik Hearthwise acts next. Combat round 2 remains active until Eirik completes his turn.",
  "narration": "Scout Kira takes aim and fires her shortbow, but the bolt sails wide, missing the second bandit. Unfazed, she closes the distance swiftly and slashes with her shortsword, the blade biting deeply into his arm. Blood wells from the fresh wound as the bandit snarls, retreating slightly under the pain.\n\nThe battle ebbs and flows—Scout Kira's strike leaves the bandit wounded but still standing. Now, the moment comes for you, Eirik Hearthwise. The foe is bruised and vulnerable; how will you press the attack?",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit_2 takes 6 slashing damage from Scout Kira's shortsword attack, HP reduced from 11 to 5."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 continuing. Eirik Hearthwise intends to cast Sacred Flame cantrip on Bandit_2. Bandit_2 must make a Dexterity saving throw DC 13. Roll d20 and add +1 dexterity modifier for save. Await player's roll for Dexterity saving throw. Damage if failed is 1d8 radiant damage from generic dice pool. Combat round 2 remains active until Eirik completes his turn.",
  "narration": "You channel divine light, invoking the sacred flame to manifest against your wounded foe. A radiant burst of searing energy crackles forth, targeting the second bandit's will and reflexes.\n\nHe must make a Dexterity saving throw against your spell’s power. Roll a d20 and add +1. If he fails, the celestial fire will scorch him mercilessly. The battle's hue shifts as holy light clashes with shadow and steel.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 concludes with all living creatures having acted: Bandit_2 (HP 1), Scout Kira, and Eirik Hearthwise. Combat round increments to 3. Bandit_2 acts first this new round. Combat round 3 begins with Bandit_2 taking its turn using prerolls available.",
  "narration": "The sacred flame bursts of radiant light scorch the wounded bandit, leaving him barely standing, one breath from collapse. The air thickens with tension as the fierce battle of wills draws to a close for this round.\n\nWith heavy breaths and tightened grips, the combatants steel themselves anew. The third round dawns sharp and unforgiving. The wounded bandit snarls, readying to strike back first in this fresh cycle of violence.\n\nBrace yourself, Eirik Hearthwise. The fight rages on, with the bandit moving first this round.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3 begins. Bandit_2 acts first with two attacks: scimitar attack roll 9 and light crossbow attack roll 2, both against Eirik Hearthwise AC 16. Followed by Scout Kira with two attacks: shortbow attack roll 7 and shortsword attack roll 1 against Bandit_2 AC 12. Eirik Hearthwise acts last. Await resolution of creature attacks.",
  "narration": "The battered bandit grits his teeth, swinging his scimitar with strained effort but missing you narrowly. Frustrated, he takes quick aim with his light crossbow, but the bolt skitters harmlessly past.\n\nScout Kira steps forward, calculating her chances—her shortbow sings a deadly note, yet the arrow veers wide. Undeterred, she lunges with her shortsword, only to be parried deftly by the bandit.\n\nThe battlefield tightens, the dust and morning haze swirling like a tempest. Now, Eirik Hearthwise, the moment to decide is yours—strike true and shift the tide of this fight.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3 continuing. Eirik Hearthwise declared a mace attack on Bandit_2 with AC 12. Awaiting player to roll d20 and add +4 for attack roll. If hit, await damage roll of 1d6 + 2. Combat round 3 remains active until Eirik completes his turn.",
  "narration": "You grip your mace firmly, the weight comfortable in your hand as you step toward the wounded bandit. The morning air bristles with tension, and your eyes lock on your target. Let your mace swing with purpose—roll a d20 and add 4 to see if your strike lands against the bandit's armor.\n\nYour blow could tip the scales. Strike true, Eirik Hearthwise.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Eirik Hearthwise attack roll 19 against Bandit_2 AC 12 hits. Awaiting player to roll damage 1d6 + 2 for mace attack. Combat round 3 remains active until Eirik completes his turn.",
  "narration": "Your mace swings in a wide arc, striking the wounded bandit solidly. The heavy blow lands true, cracking armor and flesh. Roll 1d6 and add 2 to measure the full impact of your strike and see how deeply your weapon bites into the enemy's defenses.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3 continues. Eirik's mace attack hits Bandit_2 dealing 5 bludgeoning damage reducing Bandit_2 HP from 5 to 0, killing it. All enemies are now dead, so the encounter ends immediately. Combat ends and exit action triggered.",
  "narration": "Your mace smashes down with crushing force on the wounded bandit. A pained grunt escapes him before he collapses heavily to the ground, defeated and motionless. The eerie quiet of the North Tower Overlook settles as the last threat falls.\n\nScout Kira lowers her weapons, her eyes scanning the empty battlefield, a triumphant smile breaking across her face. The danger is passed, the tower secured.\n\nVictory is yours, Eirik Hearthwise. The watchtower's grim silence now holds the promise of safety and new beginnings.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "RO06-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit_2 takes 5 bludgeoning damage from Eirik's mace attack and dies, HP 0, status dead."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

Combat Summary: {
  "narration": "As dawn breaks over the mist-shrouded ruins of the North Tower Overlook, two rugged bandits barred the path, weapons gleaming in the pale light. The battle erupted swiftly; the first bandit launched a scimitar strike, then a crossbow bolt, both thwarted by Eirik Hearthwise's steadfast defense. Scout Kira's arrow found its mark, wounding the lead bandit and setting the stage for Eirik's decisive bolt, which felled him. The second bandit, wounded but fierce, pressed the attack, landing a painful crossbow hit on Eirik before Kira's shortsword drew blood. Eirik's sacred flame forced the bandit to the brink, and in the third round, after the bandit’s feeble attack and Kira’s close attempt, Eirik's mace strike dealt a finishing blow, sending the last foe crashing down. With both bandits defeated and the tower secure, victory was well earned. Experience points totaling 50 XP were awarded—25 each to Eirik Hearthwise and Scout Kira for their coordinated efforts.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Eirik Hearthwise",
        "changes": "HP reduced to 9/11 from crossbow bolt damage; remains alive and unconditioned; used 1 Level 1 spell slot"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "North Tower Overlook Ambush",
        "changes": "Bandit defeated; status dead; HP 0/11"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "North Tower Overlook Ambush",
        "changes": "Bandit_2 wounded; HP reduced to 0/11 after mace strike; status dead"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Scout Kira",
        "changes": "HP remains 10/10; alive and unconditioned"
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit"
    }
  ]
}
